# Directory Policy (Always)

## Canonical Documentation Locations

### ALLOWED Locations

✅ **Root Directory** (essential only, STRICT 3 files)
- README.md (required)
- QUICK_START.md (required)
- QUICK_REFERENCE.md (recommended)
- **NO OTHER DOCUMENTATION ALLOWED** - All other docs must be in designated directories

✅ **docs/** (canonical internal documentation)
- docs/_system/ (governance tracking)
- docs/architecture/ (system architecture)
- docs/api/ (API documentation)
- docs/governance/ (internal governance)
- docs/guides/ (how-to guides)
- docs/reference/ (reference docs)
- docs/migrations/ (historical, excluded from AI)
- docs/changelog/ (historical, excluded from AI)

✅ **content/** (public Nextra documentation)
- content/governance/sealed/ (immutable foundation)
- content/governance/active/ (current governance)
- content/governance/amendments/ (governance amendments)
- content/guides/ (user guides)
- content/product/ (product docs)

✅ **.cursor/** (Cursor AI configuration)
- .cursor/rules/ (Cursor rules, .mdc files)
- .cursor/docs/ (Cursor-specific docs)
- .cursor/templates/ (plan templates)
- .cursor/skills/ (agent skills)
- .cursor/work/ (temporary analysis, excluded from AI)
- .cursor/archive/ (historical, excluded from AI)

✅ **.temp-docs/** (temporary holding, 7-day expiry)

### FORBIDDEN Locations

❌ **Root Directory** (except 3 essential files)
- Only README.md, QUICK_START.md, QUICK_REFERENCE.md allowed
- All other documentation MUST be in designated directories
- No exceptions for system docs, reference docs, or strategy docs

❌ **.vscode/** (config only)
- Only README.md allowed (exception granted)

❌ **Code Directories** (no standalone docs)
- src/, app/, components/, lib/ (code only)
- Exception: page-level .mdx files (Next.js convention)

