## Document Types (Frontmatter Required)

Every document MUST declare:

```yaml
---
doc_type: [CONSTITUTION|STANDARD|ADR|SPEC|PRD|RUNBOOK|POLICY|NOTE|GUIDE]
status: [draft|active|sealed|legacy|archived]
owner: [team-or-role]
source_of_truth: [true|false]
created: [YYYY-MM-DD]
modified: [YYYY-MM-DD]
tags: [tag1, tag2, ...]
---
```

### Document Type Definitions

| Type | Location | Purpose |
|------|----------|---------|
| CONSTITUTION | content/governance/sealed/ | Foundational, immutable |
| STANDARD | docs/architecture/ | Engineering standard, versioned |
| ADR | docs/architecture/adr/ | Architecture decision, immutable once ratified |
| SPEC | docs/architecture/ or docs/api/ | Technical specification, versioned |
| PRD | docs/product/ | Product requirements, versioned |
| RUNBOOK | docs/guides/ | Operational procedure, versioned |
| POLICY | docs/governance/ | Compliance policy, versioned |
| NOTE | .cursor/work/ | Working note, temporary |
| GUIDE | docs/guides/ or content/guides/ | How-to guide, versioned |

### Status Definitions

| Status | Location | Mutability |
|--------|----------|------------|
| draft | .cursor/work/ or docs/*/draft/ | Mutable |
| active | docs/*/ or content/*/active/ | Versioned |
| sealed | content/governance/sealed/ | Immutable |
| legacy | .cursor/archive/legacy/ | Read-only |
| archived | .cursor/archive/*/ | Read-only |

